10/02/2011
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- President Demetris Christofias and Turkish Cypriot leader Dervis Eroglu agreed on Wednesday (February 9th) to intensify talks to reunify the divided island. From now on, the two leaders will meet once a week and their special representatives will meet two times a week. The announcement followed talks between Christofias and Eroglu in Nicosia, as part of ongoing efforts to find a settlement to the long-standing Cypriot issue. (CNA, Anadolu news agency, Hurriyet - 09/02/11)
